<item>
            <title>[HBASE-27321] The ReplicationLogCleaner is not thread safe but can be called from different threads at the same time</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-27321</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In preClean method we will update the class fields and then use them in the getDeletableFiles method. This implies that we will have only one cleaner run at the same time.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But actually, in MasterRpcServices.runCleanerChore, we will call execute the HFileCleaner and LogCleaner directly, not in the cleanerChore thread.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This could cause data loss for replication, which is a very serious problem.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13478310">HBASE-27321</key>
